It is composed of units. Therefore, a 3x3x3 cube has 27 units that can be accessed by their positions along the x, y, and z axes. Similarly, a hyper-cube is composed of cubes, just as a cube is composed of units. Each cube in the hyper-cube can be accessed by its position relative to the hyper-cube along the x, y, and z axes. Hence, a hyper-cube of 3x3x3 will have 27 cubes. p.font: A cube in CubeCL is actually a cuboid, meaning each axis can have different lengths. It is composed of units. Therefore, a 3x3x3 cube has 27 units that can be accessed by their positions along the x, y, and z axes. Similarly, a hyper-cube is composed of cubes, just as a cube is composed of units. Each cube in the hyper-cube can be accessed by its position relative to the hyper-cube along the x, y, and z axes. Hence, a hyper-cube of 3x3x3 will have 27 cubes. In this example, the total number of working units would be 27 x 27 = 729.
